# Tailwind CSS & Styling Guidelines

## Tailwind CSS Best Practices

- Use utility classes for styling
- Prefer Tailwind classes over custom CSS
- Use responsive prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`)
- Leverage dark mode with `dark:` prefix
- Use CSS variables for theming (defined in [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css))

## Design System

The project uses a consistent design system with:

- **Colors**: Neutral base with semantic color tokens
- **Spacing**: Consistent spacing scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64px)
- **Typography**: Inter font family with proper hierarchy
- **Borders**: Consistent border radius and styles
- **Shadows**: Subtle shadows for depth

## Component Styling

- Use shadcn/ui components as base
- Extend with Tailwind classes for customization
- Maintain consistent spacing and typography
- Use semantic color tokens for accessibility

## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first approach
- Use responsive breakpoints consistently
- Test on multiple screen sizes
- Use container queries when appropriate

## Dark Mode Support

- Always include dark mode variants
- Use CSS variables for theme switching
- Test both light and dark themes
- Ensure proper contrast ratios

## Example Styling Patterns

```tsx
// Responsive card with dark mode
<Card className="w-full md:w-1/2 lg:w-1/3 bg-white dark:bg-slate-800">
  <CardHeader className="p-6">
    <CardTitle className="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">
      Title
    </CardTitle>
  </CardHeader>
</Card>

// Button with variants
<Button 
  variant="outline" 
  size="lg" 
  className="w-full sm:w-auto hover:bg-slate-50 dark:hover:bg-slate-800"
>
  Action
</Button>
```